com.jpl.nasa.scihound

Class AdminInformation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jpl.nasa.scihound.AdminInformation

  • public class AdminInformation
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that holds the Admin-set information. The admin's email, verification password, and compression quality information is held in this class.

      • compressionQuality

        public static int compressionQuality
        Values must be in [0,100]. (High Quality : (90,100], Medium Quality : (80,90], Low Quality : (70,80]). The lower the quality the more points with images can be collected. 80 allows ~24 points with pictures to be collected.

      • maxPoints

        public static final int maxPoints
        Number of points that we're limiting the user to collect in a single session.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • minNumOfSatellites

        public static int minNumOfSatellites
        Minimum number of satellites that the application should be seeing before collecting a point. Empirically, we see that when the application sees 15 to 17 satellites it will have an accuracy reading < 5 meters. The admin can set how strict the application is, by either increasing or decreasing this number.

      • sendType

        public static java.lang.String sendType
        The type of medium used for sending the points and the images. Right now we are expecting either points sent to a server or to an email.
